5:
UGH. What a waste of time! 
Those grody guildies wouldn't know 
treasure if it slapped them in the face!
15:
Yeah. TOTAL bust though. 
They didn't even know what to do with 
this treasure, let alone price it!
17:
Perhaps the scientists in the Great Blue 
might know something... Or maybe an 
alchemist.
20:
Treasure? 
You mean the junk in your hands?
24:
It isn't junk! 
This Star Teardrop here is something 
I picked up in another world, you see, 
and—
39:
World Flipper activated... 
Prepare for launch.
51:
Give me a... warning next time... 
My head's killing me—
56: Wait. It can't be! Could this really be...
58:
Shinjuku! It's Shinjuku! 
How did you find it?
59: This is the world I'm from!
69:
What are you talking about? 
Look at the skyscrapers! 
The hustle and bustle of the city!
74: Wait... no one's looking our way.
75:
I don't feel a thing, either. 
Alk, what are you seeing right now?
79:
Not a thing. Just... darkness. 
I'd very much like to go now.
86:
This appears to be Starview Village, 
but... There's no one here.
93:
Stella?! 
Get a hold of yourself!
97:
Starview... It's been destroyed! 
Everything is in shambles!
101:
Stay calm, you two! 
Listen to me and listen close. 
This kind of thing happens sometimes.
111:
It's a phenomenon often experienced 
on long voyages... 
You start seeing things that aren't there
—ghost ships, or non-existent islands!
115:
They can be things you've dreamed of, 
things you've lost, or your worst fears. 
Mirages are unpredictable like that.
123:
That's right! But we can't let some silly 
illusions get in the way of THIS ship! 
It's full sail ahead, baby! Right?
126:
You're right. 
We cannot allow ourselves to stop 
here.
129:
Yeah! 
Who cares if we can't see what's ahead? 
As long as we keep pushing forward... 
whichever way that is!
132:
That's the spirit! 
Now... watch a real captain in action!
134:
All these mirages will be gone by 
morning! 
And you can count on that!
141: Indeed. We've been here once before.
145:
Oh. I guess we're all seeing the same 
thing now, right?
156:
Finally. 
I guess we can finally wrap up this 
adventure.
159:
Yeah, one that was triggered that 
"treasure" of yours.
162:
Was it, now? 
Sorry, I'm a bit fuzzy on the details—
what matters is that we all learned 
something, right?
165:
So c'mon, let's go back already and get 
ready for our next REAL adventure!
169:
Agreed.
Activating World Flipper... 
Prepare for launch.
